84
00:12:23,220 --> 00:12:31,080
facing so many beautiful seekers.

85
00:12:31,080 --> 00:12:34,320
If you ask Me, "When did You go to Brazil?"

86
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:37,000
I won't be able to tell you the dates.

87
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:44,080
I have very bad memory for dates for the same
reason, I think, because every time I see

88
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:46,290
a vision.

89
00:12:46,290 --> 00:12:54,160
And the time also just stops for that moment.

90
00:12:54,160 --> 00:12:58,520
It doesn't express itself.

91
00:12:58,520 --> 00:13:03,880
Nothing is recorded, except for the experience.

92
00:13:03,880 --> 00:13:11,710
And this experience is in an abstract form.

93
00:13:11,710 --> 00:13:15,250
You cannot describe.

94
00:13:15,250 --> 00:13:24,170
It is beyond words and beyond any description.

95
00:13:24,170 --> 00:13:42,300
At that time you really become thoughtless,
and that is the time we have to really enjoy.

96
00:13:42,300 --> 00:13:45,390
         
The greatest curse of modern times is the

97
00:13:45,390 --> 00:13:50,700
watch, all the time that we keep.

98
00:13:50,700 --> 00:14:04,860
And all the time we are just seeing the time,
what time it is now, and after two seconds

99
00:14:04,860 --> 00:14:11,360
again also you want to see what is the time.

100
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:16,320
We have crossed the limits of time – kalatit.

101
00:14:16,320 --> 00:14:22,980
Try to understand why we have crossed, because
time moves according to us.

102
00:14:22,980 --> 00:14:28,420
You can experience it.

103
00:14:28,420 --> 00:14:36,490
The other day I was coming from Delhi, and
in My household everybody seems to be very

104
00:14:36,490 --> 00:14:39,430
particular about time.

105
00:14:39,430 --> 00:14:41,760
So they were after My life, "Come along, come
along.

106
00:14:41,760 --> 00:14:42,900
Getting late, getting late.

107
00:14:42,900 --> 00:14:47,960
Now, you can't just get into the plane," this,
that.

108
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:50,150
All right.

109
00:14:50,150 --> 00:14:54,370
And when I reached there, they said that "The
plane is still waiting.

110
00:14:54,370 --> 00:14:58,170
It's not … it's not necessary for you to
hurry up.

111
00:14:58,170 --> 00:15:03,620
It will take at least fifteen, twenty minutes
for you to go."

112
00:15:03,620 --> 00:15:09,740
So, also this name of "airport" makes people
really jumpy, I should say.

113
00:15:09,740 --> 00:15:15,740
They have to go to the aeroplane means as
if some war is there or I don't know what

114
00:15:15,740 --> 00:15:19,470
it is.

115
00:15:19,470 --> 00:15:25,900
So far, luckily, I have never missed a plane,
never missed a train in My lifetime.

116
00:15:25,900 --> 00:15:30,190
Though I travel, I think, quite a lot.

117
00:15:30,190 --> 00:15:40,029
I have every time found, invariably, that
the plane itself is waiting for Me.

118
00:15:40,029 --> 00:15:41,820
It won't leave.

119
00:15:41,820 --> 00:15:49,370
Like, I'll give you a very interesting example
today, if you are relaxed.

120
00:15:49,370 --> 00:16:09,899
We were in Prague, and we were supposed to
go to Poland via – again same thing happens

121
00:16:09,899 --> 00:16:14,680
to Me with experience I had – via Vienna.

122
00:16:14,680 --> 00:16:20,620
And we had a very great Sahaja yogi with us
who told Me that the plane will be leaving

123
00:16:20,620 --> 00:16:23,420
at eleven o'clock.

124
00:16:23,420 --> 00:16:27,080
And from the airport he rings Me up, "No,
the plane is leaving at 9:30."

125
00:16:27,080 --> 00:16:34,520
If I want, I can be ready in five minutes
or I can take two hours, depends on.

126
00:16:34,520 --> 00:16:35,520
So I was ready.

127
00:16:35,520 --> 00:16:36,580
I just jumped into the car.

128
00:16:36,580 --> 00:16:43,640
We reached the airport, but we were late by
fifteen minutes, and the ground lady started

129
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:50,830
shouting at Me at the top of her voice, "You
people, you are VIPs, you are this, you are

130
00:16:50,830 --> 00:16:51,830
that."

131
00:16:51,830 --> 00:16:54,120
All kinds of things she said to Me.

132
00:16:54,120 --> 00:16:57,589
And this Sahaja yogi could not bear it.

133
00:16:57,589 --> 00:17:04,720
And he felt that it was his mistake – he
told Me a wrong time, “That's why this lady

134
00:17:04,720 --> 00:17:07,589
is shouting at my Mother.”

135
00:17:07,589 --> 00:17:13,700
He couldn't bear it.

136
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:19,810
He was very unhappy.

137
00:17:19,810 --> 00:17:33,929
So, we went into the aeroplane with this lady
shouting behind, and we saw that the pilot

138
00:17:33,929 --> 00:17:38,990
and engineers, they were busy with some correction
of the machinery.

139
00:17:38,990 --> 00:17:42,050
They said, "It is little bit out of order.

140
00:17:42,050 --> 00:17:43,050
It will be ready."

141
00:17:43,050 --> 00:17:44,180
So we sat down.

142
00:17:44,180 --> 00:17:52,510
Now this Sahaja yogi could not bear it, and
his tears started rolling down his eyes.

143
00:17:52,510 --> 00:17:56,420
The another Sahaj yogini, she said, “Brother,
it's all right.

144
00:17:56,420 --> 00:17:57,990
Don't cry."

145
00:17:57,990 --> 00:17:59,000
They were sitting behind Me.

146
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:00,330
I just turned round.

147
00:18:00,330 --> 00:18:03,810
I said, "It's all right.

148
00:18:03,810 --> 00:18:04,810
Don't worry."

149
00:18:04,810 --> 00:18:08,190
He said, "No Mother, because of me she could
say all these things, you know.

150
00:18:08,190 --> 00:18:09,830
I can't bear it."

151
00:18:09,830 --> 00:18:12,980
And he couldn't stop crying.

152
00:18:12,980 --> 00:18:25,440
Within one minute, the sky which was absolutely
open was covered with big clouds like huge,

153
00:18:25,440 --> 00:18:30,370
big elephants walking into the whole area
– very big.

154
00:18:30,370 --> 00:18:40,360
All the Sahaja yogis who were standing also
– on the other side, on top of the airport

155
00:18:40,360 --> 00:18:42,450
– saw it happening.

156
00:18:42,450 --> 00:18:45,010
The whole thing became absolutely jet-black.

157
00:18:45,010 --> 00:18:48,300
"Oh, My God," I said.

158
00:18:48,300 --> 00:18:53,300
"See, the tears of this gentleman has such
powers."

159
00:18:53,300 --> 00:19:01,120
And then the airport people told us that this
plane is out of order, so we have to get down.

160
00:19:01,120 --> 00:19:03,410
So we got down.

161
00:19:03,410 --> 00:19:05,140
We came back.

162
00:19:05,140 --> 00:19:13,090
Then he went to this ground hostess and told
her, "Now, whom should we shout at?

163
00:19:13,090 --> 00:19:16,480
Now the plane is not going, should we shout
at you?

164
00:19:16,480 --> 00:19:20,340
How dare you shout at my Mother and all those
things you said?"

165
00:19:20,340 --> 00:19:31,830
But all the people there at the airport, who
were still in … under the same regime style,

166
00:19:31,830 --> 00:19:33,990
got such a fright.

167
00:19:33,990 --> 00:19:36,740
The manager himself walked to Me.

168
00:19:36,740 --> 00:19:42,620
He said, "For your plane there's still five
hours and if you want out we can give you

169
00:19:42,620 --> 00:19:44,580
permission, all of you can go out."

170
00:19:44,580 --> 00:19:47,059
And he took Me by a special way.

171
00:19:47,059 --> 00:19:50,490
I couldn't understand this reaction.

172
00:19:50,490 --> 00:19:57,750
So I went out and we did some shopping or
something, and when we came back we were surprised.

173
00:19:57,750 --> 00:20:04,780
All the airport was rather stunned by us and
when I walked – that was the only plane

174
00:20:04,780 --> 00:20:10,210
that was leaving – all the traffic had stopped
except for this plane.

175
00:20:10,210 --> 00:20:19,830
And when we walked down to board the plane,
the gentleman who was there said, "Mother,

176
00:20:19,830 --> 00:20:22,760
can you help me?"

177
00:20:22,760 --> 00:20:23,760
I said, "How?"

178
00:20:23,760 --> 00:20:24,960
"I have got a terrible back pain."

179
00:20:24,960 --> 00:20:27,630
I said, "How can I do it?"

180
00:20:27,630 --> 00:20:32,730
Then one lady walked in to say, "Mother, please,
I have pain in my shoulder.

181
00:20:32,730 --> 00:20:35,880
Can you put your hand on that?"

182
00:20:35,880 --> 00:20:39,900
I just put My hand on her shoulder and she
said, "I am feeling all right."

183
00:20:39,900 --> 00:20:42,610
She started lifting her arm.

184
00:20:42,610 --> 00:20:50,890
Then I went – I thought I'd better now take
to the aeroplane – when I was walking, the

185
00:20:50,890 --> 00:20:52,540
same gentleman came to Me.

186
00:20:52,540 --> 00:20:55,210
He said, "Why not put hand on my back?"

187
00:20:55,210 --> 00:20:57,610
I said, "I have to board the plane."

188
00:20:57,610 --> 00:20:59,370
He said, "I'll walk with You.

189
00:20:59,370 --> 00:21:01,490
You just put your hand on my back.

190
00:21:01,490 --> 00:21:03,140
I'm sure I'll be all right."

191
00:21:03,140 --> 00:21:06,160
And we walked together about two minutes or
so.

192
00:21:06,160 --> 00:21:09,130
He said, "I'm all right."

193
00:21:09,130 --> 00:21:12,180
The whole atmosphere changed.

194
00:21:12,180 --> 00:21:19,630
It was such a tremendous effect on these people
who have been under a regime and have been

195
00:21:19,630 --> 00:21:24,080
really military-like, and the whole treatment
was so funny.

196
00:21:24,080 --> 00:21:35,270
The whole thing changed in such a short time,
and I was amazed how the tears of this Sahaja

197
00:21:35,270 --> 00:21:38,290
yogi has worked this wonder.

198
00:21:38,290 --> 00:21:48,860
Now, imagine a moment when tears started rolling
his eyes, that moment just manifested a big

199
00:21:48,860 --> 00:21:49,900
drama.

200
00:21:49,900 --> 00:22:02,470
And, ultimately, what you find is that the
people at the airport became extremely humble

201
00:22:02,470 --> 00:22:07,600
and respectful.

202
00:22:07,600 --> 00:22:13,390
         
So when we start thinking of time and time

203
00:22:13,390 --> 00:22:21,600
and time, we have to understand that time
is our slave.

204
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:23,880
We are not slaves of the time.

205
00:22:23,880 --> 00:22:32,840
There are thousand and one stories I can tell
you how, by delaying in a place, by getting

206
00:22:32,840 --> 00:22:42,110
late in a place, by not caring for the time,
I have seen such beautiful manifestations,

207
00:22:42,110 --> 00:22:53,960
such beautiful dramas – the art of the divine
power – that I was amazed how people worry

208
00:22:53,960 --> 00:22:58,429
so much about the time.

209
00:22:58,429 --> 00:23:11,860
If time is really necessary, if we are all
watching our time every year, as our birthday,

210
00:23:11,860 --> 00:23:18,200
and if you think that time is very important,
it is in a way.

211
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:27,040
In these modern times, we really need the
time for meditation, for collective meetings

212
00:23:27,040 --> 00:23:31,830
and for Sahaja Yoga.

213
00:23:31,830 --> 00:23:40,780
I know when there was the war of independence
in this country, where My parents fought with

214
00:23:40,780 --> 00:23:46,820
all their tana, mana, dhana [trans: body,
mind, wealth].

215
00:23:46,820 --> 00:23:51,820
That time I remember how they never cared
for anything.

216
00:23:51,820 --> 00:24:02,730
They went all out, because it was very important
to get this country freed from the clutches

217
00:24:02,730 --> 00:24:06,510
of the Empire.

218
00:24:06,510 --> 00:24:12,640
And this was so important.

219
00:24:12,640 --> 00:24:19,880
They had to meet somebody at such a point:
that man, supposing, is escaping from the

220
00:24:19,880 --> 00:24:25,460
jail, or there's some sort of a thing on,
they could not afford to miss the time.

221
00:24:25,460 --> 00:24:34,220
They could not afford to just neglect that
important time, important meeting, important

222
00:24:34,220 --> 00:24:38,580
discussion, because everything had become
an emergency.

223
00:24:38,580 --> 00:24:44,820
For them, nobody told them, nobody gave them
lectures, but for them, from inside.

224
00:24:44,820 --> 00:24:53,680
They were all legendary people, I should say,
the way they fought for their freedom.

225
00:24:53,680 --> 00:24:57,020
         
This is, today, the same situation.

226
00:24:57,020 --> 00:25:02,670
It is an emergency, a very subtle emergency.

227
00:25:02,670 --> 00:25:10,670
That nothing is more important than spreading
Sahaja Yoga.

228
00:25:10,670 --> 00:25:18,120
If some people will miss it, will not know
about it, we will be responsible for that.

229
00:25:18,120 --> 00:25:26,049
At the time of Christ, Buddha, Mahavira or
any one of them, there were no aeroplanes

230
00:25:26,049 --> 00:25:28,390
to travel.

